    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok, this deck bids 7 to go first on a regular basis. I bid 8 at the TOC a few times and I was still alright. The deck starts with Sam and Arwen, or if you know your opponent is playing Uruk-hai, start Legolas.  If for some reason you are outbid, start all the hobbits.  Pippin is used to remove a burden off Frodo.  In the games that I played, I always went first. <br />
     <br />
The deck will explode all at once, and you need to be willing to lose people like crazy.  Bolger is a huge help in this game, especially if you get him early, as hobbits have a lot of health.  I realize this deck does not look as good on paper as it does when it plays, but trust me it works.  The extra Gandalfs help in healing the son of Drogo.  There were numerous times when i healed frodo, then pitched a copy of Gandy to heal him. <br />
<br />
The shadow side is mostly guys.  It just relentlessly beats on people. Since it is such a small deck, the guys come out quick and armors and even archery have little matter. People will stop. <br />
<br />
Sadly, I dont see this deck working too well post ROTEL.  I hope you consider that while rating this, also consider it took first place, going 6-1.  <br />
<br />
Thanks again Gabe, and if you read this, I need your home phone number, your cell is off.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
